 Britney Spears | Photo RCA Records Britney Spears has said that nail art saved her through her anxiety.
The ‘Circus’ singer made this known on her Instagram page just as she enjoys her newfound freedom. Where she told fans that nail art helped her find her confidence while she was struggling with anxiety and dealing with her family feud.
The 40year old singer proudly showed off her beautifully embellished nails. With it, she wrote ‘‘Have people been out on me because I’ve never seen these before! The most adorable little charms I’ve ever seen in my life!’’ She goes on to write in her post which expresses how she has tried to cope in life she wrote ‘‘I’ve felt ghosted all my life but if you feel somewhat not acknowledged enough in life or have confidence problems, I swear these charms do not acknowledge enough in life or have confidence problems, I swear these charms do in fact change your perspective!!!’’
‘‘For instance, I never talked because I’m usually shy, I have social anxiety but like the worst kind where it’s unbearable but holy s***there’s hope!!!
Britney Spears summed up the post with a joke about her small hands and asked her fan base not to laugh.
This was followed by heartwarming messages from her fans one wrote ‘‘There are so many fun things to explore! You go B, you deserve ALL THE CHARMS.’’ 